#Purpose:is to write a Python program (script) that is given an amount in fluid ounces and converts it to an equivalent amount in gallons, quarts, pints, cups and ounces. To calculate and display values of (cos(x) + i*sin(x))**n,cos(n*x) + i*sin(n*x), whether or not (cos(x) + i*sin(x))**n is equal to cos(n*x) + i*sin(n*x) and the difference (cos(x) + i*sin(x))n - cos(n*x) + i*sin(n*x) in a table,where x is an angle in radians and n is some real number
#rem1 = remainder of gallon from a fluid 
#rem2 = remainder of quarts from a gallon
#rem3 = remainder of pint from a quarts
#rem4 = remainder of cup from a pint

from time import ctime
print('-'*80)
fluid = int(input('Enter a measurement in ounces; '))
gallon = fluid // 128
rem1 = fluid % 128
quart = rem1 // 32
rem2 = rem1 % 32
pint = rem2 // 16
rem3 = rem2 % 16
cup = rem3 // 8
rem4 = rem3 % 8
ounce = rem4
print('''
%d ounces is equivalent to: 
%d gallons +
%d quarts +
%d pint +
%d cup +
%d ounces ''' % (fluid,gallon,quart,pint,cup,ounce))


print("""
Programmed by Jabo Conrad 
Date: %s
End of Processing.""" %ctime())
